Package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.validator

Class TableAssertionFunctions

java.lang.Object
io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.validator.TableAssertionFunctions
public class TableAssertionFunctions extends Object
Provides a set of validation functions for asserting table data integrity.

This class includes various validation methods to check the state of table elements, such as row counts, uniqueness, presence of values, and cell properties (e.g., enabled, clickable).

    • validateAllCellsClickable

      public static boolean validateAllCellsClickable(Object actual, Object expected)
      Validates whether all cells in the table are clickable.

      A cell is considered clickable if it is a SmartWebElement, is displayed, and is enabled. This method ensures that every row in the table contains only clickable elements.

      Parameters:
      actual - The table data (expected to be a List of lists, where each inner list represents a row).
      expected - The expected state (a Boolean, where true means all cells should be clickable).
      Returns:
      true if all cells in the table are clickable and match the expected state; otherwise, false.
